get.description:
**Purpose:** Stream real-time deployment/destroy logs via Server-Sent Events.

**When to call:** After POST to /deploy or /destroy returns session_id.

**Connection:** Open as EventSource in browser/HTTP client.

**SSE event types:**
- `log`: Line of output {id, data, level, timestamp}
- `heartbeat`: Keep-alive (via SSE comment)
- `complete`: Success {status, message, outputs}
- `error`: Failure {status, message}

**Reconnection:** Pass `last_event_id` query param to resume from event ID.

**Timeout:** Heartbeats sent every 30s to keep connection alive.

**Purpose:** Real-time SSE stream of log entries matching the trace_id.

**When to call:** After `startLogTrace` returns, connect to this SSE endpoint.

**SSE event types:**
- `log`: Individual log entry {prefix, timestamp, message, layer, provider}
- `error`: Error during trace {message}
- `done`: Trace complete {summary with counts per provider/layer}

**Timeout:** Stream closes after ~30s or when 'done' event is sent.
